text: {{Infobox settlement | name = Pärnu County | settlement_type = County of Estonia | image_skyline = Pärnu jõgi Toris.jpg | image_flag = Pärnumaa_lipp.svg | flag_size = 125px | image_shield = Et-Pärnu maakond-coa.svg | shield_size = 75px | image_map = Pärnu County in Estonia.svg | subdivision_type = Country | subdivision_name = Estonia | seat_type = Capital | seat = Pärnu | leader_title = Governor | leader_name = | area_total_km2 = 4806.68 | population_total = 84,462 | population_as_of = Jan 2017 |population_rank = | population_density_km2 = auto | registration_plate = F | iso_code = EE-67 | website = | footnotes = }} Pärnu County is a county in Estonia. The capital city is also named Pärnu. It is on the coast of the Gulf of Riga. The county is divided into municipalities. There is one urban municipality and six rural municipalities in Pärnu County.
